of electricity.

00:10:19.850 --> 00:10:22.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's, in fact, that that
we promise to our people.

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:24.840 align:middle line:84%
We will use the rivers
and the running water

00:10:24.840 --> 00:10:27.520 align:middle line:84%
to provide our own
supply of electricity.

00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:30.730 align:middle line:84%
And that electricity will
be free to all the people.

00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:33.450 align:middle line:84%
Free electricity for
everyone, as long

00:10:33.450 --> 00:10:37.320 align:middle line:84%
as they contribute three hours
a week to one of the community

00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:39.270 align:middle line:90%
projects that we set up.

00:10:39.270 --> 00:10:41.560 align:middle line:84%
So let's go through
the scenario again.

00:10:41.560 --> 00:10:43.430 align:middle line:90%
We win a campaign.

00:10:43.430 --> 00:10:46.120 align:middle line:84%
We win the elections
in a small town.

00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:50.280 align:middle line:84%
The Ubuntu mayor start to
implement the simple philosophy

00:10:50.280 --> 00:10:52.170 align:middle line:90%
of community projects.

00:10:52.170 --> 00:10:55.270 align:middle line:84%
We set up a wide variety
of community projects

00:10:55.270 --> 00:10:59.000 align:middle line:84%
that actually benefit the people
of the town, not corporations

00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:02.260 align:middle line:84%
or the municipality
or the government.

00:11:02.260 --> 00:11:05.500 align:middle line:84%
The community projects must be
there to benefit the people.

00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:09.230 align:middle line:84%
And remember that we still live
in a world driven by money.

00:11:09.230 --> 00:11:12.350 align:middle line:84%
So we need to use money to
set up the systems to free

00:11:12.350 --> 00:11:14.050 align:middle line:90%
ourselves from the money.

00:11:14.050 --> 00:11:16.060 align:middle line:84%
Once we win the
elections, we also

00:11:16.060 --> 00:11:18.260 align:middle line:84%
get money channeled
from government.

00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:21.195 align:middle line:84%
That money right now is used and
abused by our municipalities,

00:11:21.195 --> 00:11:24.660 align:middle line:84%
by our mayors, for their
own personal agenda, to buy

00:11:24.660 --> 00:11:26.580 align:middle line:90%
fancy cars and fancy houses.

00:11:26.580 --> 00:11:28.810 align:middle line:84%
We see virtually
no money that gets

00:11:28.810 --> 00:11:31.210 align:middle line:84%
channeled into
upgrading our towns

00:11:31.210 --> 00:11:33.550 align:middle line:84%
and providing facilities
for the people.

00:11:33.550 --> 00:11:36.150 align:middle line:84%
Once we start funneling
and channeling this money

00:11:36.150 --> 00:11:38.270 align:middle line:84%
into setting up
community projects,

00:11:38.270 --> 00:11:41.850 align:middle line:84%
people will see a rapid
change very, very quickly.

00:11:41.850 --> 00:11:44.120 align:middle line:84%
Over and above that,
community projects

00:11:44.120 --> 00:11:46.710 align:middle line:84%
will be set up that
benefit the communities.

00:11:46.710 --> 00:11:48.940 align:middle line:84%
These are not just
set up haphazardly.

00:11:48.940 --> 00:11:53.020 align:middle line:84%
They're set up with very
specific intent in mind,

00:11:53.020 --> 00:11:57.030 align:middle line:84%
and managed and set up with
master teachers or master

00:11:57.030 --> 00:12:00.360 align:middle line:84%
artisans in each one so that
we have master engineers

00:12:00.360 --> 00:12:03.050 align:middle line:84%
or scientists or
researchers or bakers

00:12:03.050 --> 00:12:06.200 align:middle line:84%
or cheesemakers or people
that run the dairy.

00:12:06.200 --> 00:12:08.910 align:middle line:84%
Each one of these would
be specifically chosen

00:12:08.910 --> 00:12:11.720 align:middle line:84%
to run that particular
community project.

00:12:11.720 --> 00:12:15.410 align:middle line:84%
And we have, at this stage,
identified about 24 community

00:12:15.410 --> 00:12:19.040 align:middle line:84%
projects to set up in our
town, in our community.

00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:21.940 align:middle line:84%
And we're using
this as an example.

00:12:21.940 --> 00:12:23.730 align:middle line:90%
What happens next?

00:12:23.730 --> 00:12:28.150 align:middle line:84%
Everyone that participates
in these community projects

00:12:28.150 --> 00:12:29.900 align:middle line:90%
gets free electricity.

00:12:29.900 --> 00:12:31.360 align:middle line:90%
It's our electricity.

00:12:31.360 --> 00:12:34.310 align:middle line:84%
We have implemented this
electricity for ourselves.

00:12:34.310 --> 00:12:38.100 align:middle line:84%
We unplug the grid that comes
from central government.

00:12:38.100 --> 00:12:41.160 align:middle line:84%
And we plug our own
electricity supply in.

00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:43.990 align:middle line:84%
The time for asking
permission is over.

00:12:43.990 --> 00:12:47.700 align:middle line:84%
We are implementing our
own election promises.

00:12:47.700 --> 00:12:50.200 align:middle line:84%
We're implementing what
we promised the people.

00:12:50.200 --> 00:12:53.890 align:middle line:84%
The people vote us in because of
what we say we're going to do.

00:12:53.890 --> 00:12:56.070 align:middle line:90%
Now we're going to do this.

00:12:56.070 --> 00:12:58.050 align:middle line:84%
I hope this is
making sense to you.

00:12:58.050 --> 00:13:00.320 align:middle line:84%
This is really important
to internalize this.

00:13:00.320 --> 00:13:02.350 align:middle line:84%
Remember, the
governments are supposed

00:13:02.350 --> 00:13:04.000 align:middle line:84%
to be the servants
of the people.

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:06.950 align:middle line:84%
The municipality is supposed
to be the local servant

00:13:06.950 --> 00:13:07.880 align:middle line:90%
of the people.

00:13:07.880 --> 00:13:10.160 align:middle line:84%
The countries belong
to the people.

00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:11.695 align:middle line:90%
The towns belong to the people.

00:13:11.695 --> 00:13:14.330 align:middle line:84%
We are taking back what
belongs to the people

00:13:14.330 --> 00:13:18.440 align:middle line:84%
and making it paradise and a
utopian place for us to live,

00:13:18.440 --> 00:13:22.240 align:middle line:84%
working in unity, working
together, collaboratively

00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:24.140 align:middle line:90%
and in collaboration.

00:13:24.140 --> 00:13:27.850 align:middle line:84%
What we do-- everybody
contributes three hours a week

00:13:27.850 --> 00:13:29.660 align:middle line:84%
towards one of these
community projects.

00:13:29.660 --> 00:13:32.760 align:middle line:84%
And in return, you
get free electricity.

00:13:32.760 --> 00:13:34.450 align:middle line:90%
But that does a lot more.

00:13:34.450 --> 00:13:38.110 align:middle line:84%
What this does is
instantly turns our town

00:13:38.110 --> 00:13:41.590 align:middle line:84%
into a powerful
united labor force.

00:13:41.590 --> 00:13:42.930 align:middle line:90%
Here's a simple example.

00:13:42.930 --> 00:13:46.730 align:middle line:84%
Our little town of 5,000
people, three hours a week,

00:13:46.730 --> 00:13:51.490 align:middle line:84%
that's equivalent to 15,000
hours of labor per week.

00:13:51.490 --> 00:13:55.210 align:middle line:84%
No corporation, no
municipality can compete

00:13:55.210 --> 00:13:56.890 align:middle line:90%
with that kind of labor force.

00:13:56.890 --> 00:13:58.960 align:middle line:84%
And I hope you
realize that this is

00:13:58.960 --> 00:14:02.450 align:middle line:84%
how quickly we can turn things
around in favor of the people.

00:14:02.450 --> 00:14:05.150 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, we're doing
things for ourselves.

00:14:05.150 --> 00:14:08.400 align:middle line:84%
And everybody has three
hours a week to contribute.

00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:10.030 align:middle line:10%
What do people get in return?

00:14:10.030 --> 00:14:10.870 align:middle line:10%
Everything.

00:14:10.870 --> 00:14:13.870 align:middle line:10%
Free electricity, free
bread, free milk, free eggs,

00:14:13.870 --> 00:14:17.980 align:middle line:10%
free furniture, free clothes,
cheese, cream, fish, shoes.

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:20.210 align:middle line:84%
Whatever we set up as
a community project,

00:14:20.210 --> 00:14:24.220 align:middle line:84%
you get for free because you
give your three hours a week.

00:14:24.220 --> 00:14:26.550 align:middle line:84%
It's a very important
thing that happens

00:14:26.550 --> 00:14:28.930 align:middle line:84%
in this transitional
phase is that you

00:14:28.930 --> 00:14:30.650 align:middle line:90%
don't have to give up your job.

00:14:30.650 --> 00:14:33.040 align:middle line:84%
And this is how
beautiful and simple

00:14:33.040 --> 00:14:34.920 align:middle line:90%
this transitional phase is.

00:14:34.920 --> 00:14:38.050 align:middle line:10%
Everyone can keep their job,
keep doing what they're doing,

00:14:38.050 --> 00:14:40.080 align:middle line:10%
and just contribute
three hours a week

00:14:40.080 --> 00:14:44.760 align:middle line:10%
as we set up these projects
and start creating abundance.

00:14:44.760 --> 00:14:47.260 align:middle line:10%
And this is where the
contributionism principle

00:14:47.260 --> 00:14:48.170 align:middle line:10%
kicks in.

00:14:48.170 --> 00:14:51.290 align:middle line:10%
We don't just make
enough for ourselves.

00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:54.690 align:middle line:10%
Remember, we are not creating
self-sustaining communities.

00:14:54.690 --> 00:14:57.400 align:middle line:84%
We are creating
communities of abundance

00:14:57.400 --> 00:15:00.230 align:middle line:84%
where we create far
more than what we need.

00:15:00.230 --> 00:15:04.185 align:middle line:84%
So we very carefully calculate
how many potatoes we need,

00:15:04.185 --> 00:15:06.310 align:middle line:84%
how much of this we need
and how much that we need.

00:15:06.310 --> 00:15:10.380 align:middle line:84%
And we create at least, at
least three times as much

00:15:10.380 --> 00:15:13.550 align:middle line:84%
as what we need for every
member of our community.

00:15:13.550 --> 00:15:16.300 align:middle line:84%
This means we'll
always have too much.

00:15:16.300 --> 00:15:20.630 align:middle line:84%
So what happens with this
excess that we create?

00:15:20.630 --> 00:15:22.695 align:middle line:84%
This is where the
abundance comes in.

00:15:22.695 --> 00:15:24.590 align:middle line:84%
In the beginning,
while we still live

00:15:24.590 --> 00:15:27.470 align:middle line:84%
in a world driven
by money, we make

00:15:27.470 --> 00:15:30.850 align:middle line:84%
this excess available to all
our surrounding communities.

00:15:30.850 --> 00:15:33.790 align:middle line:84%
But because we're doing
it ourselves for free,

00:15:33.790 --> 00:15:37.250 align:middle line:84%
we can make it available
for a very, very low cost,

00:15:37.250 --> 00:15:41.490 align:middle line:84%
at a fraction of the price that
any Walmart or any corporation

00:15:41.490 --> 00:15:45.050 align:middle line:84%
or any supermarket can sell
these items or these services

00:15:45.050 --> 00:15:46.340 align:middle line:90%
or these goods for.

00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:50.070 align:middle line:84%
We can underprice anyone,
which means we immediately

00:15:50.070 --> 00:15:52.200 align:middle line:84%
start to affect the
capitalist model

00:15:52.200 --> 00:15:55.740 align:middle line:84%
of all our neighboring towns
and as far and wide as we

00:15:55.740 --> 00:15:57.580 align:middle line:84%
distribute our
products and services

00:15:57.580 --> 00:15:59.280 align:middle line:90%
from our little community.

00:15:59.280 --> 00:16:01.690 align:middle line:84%
This will bring in
huge amounts of money

00:16:01.690 --> 00:16:04.500 align:middle line:84%
into the community coffers
and the community chest

00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:08.100 align:middle line:84%
account that is
there for the people,

00:16:08.100 --> 00:16:10.870 align:middle line:84%
not for the municipality,
for the people.

00:16:10.870 --> 00:16:14.640 align:middle line:84%
But now that the municipality
is run by the Ubuntu mayor,

00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:16.060 align:middle line:90%
everything changes.

00:16:16.060 --> 00:16:19.410 align:middle line:84%
And this money keeps getting
reinvested into the coffers

00:16:19.410 --> 00:16:23.930 align:middle line:84%
and upgrading every community
project on a regular basis.

00:16:23.930 --> 00:16:26.070 align:middle line:84%
Very quickly,
overnight, the people

00:16:26.070 --> 00:16:28.870 align:middle line:84%
in our town and our community
will see the upgrades

00:16:28.870 --> 00:16:31.320 align:middle line:84%
in the sporting facilities
and all these things

00:16:31.320 --> 00:16:34.530 align:middle line:84%
that I've mentioned, the 24
community projects that we have

00:16:34.530 --> 00:16:37.290 align:middle line:90%
mentioned in our manifesto.

00:16:37.290 --> 00:16:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And this is how rapidly
things can change.

00:16:39.700 --> 00:16:41.880 align:middle line:90%
I want to give you an example.

00:16:41.880 --> 00:16:45.320 align:middle line:84%
At the moment, we have a
fish farm in our community.

00:16:45.320 --> 00:16:47.830 align:middle line:90%
That fish farm is standing idle.

00:16:47.830 --> 00:16:52.540 align:middle line:84%
Once implemented and upgraded
and made operational,

00:16:52.540 --> 00:16:55.770 align:middle line:84%
this fish farm can breed about
a million fish per month.

00:16:55.770 --> 00:17:00.180 align:middle line:84%
That will bring arguably
about a million dollars month

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:01.710 align:middle line:90%
to our community.

00:17:01.710 --> 00:17:06.339 align:middle line:84%
This is about three times
as much as our current town

00:17:06.339 --> 00:17:07.829 align:middle line:90%
gets from government.

00:17:07.829 --> 00:17:11.790 align:middle line:84%
So this is one community project
bringing in three times as much

00:17:11.790 --> 00:17:13.720 align:middle line:90%
as government is putting in.

00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:17.109 align:middle line:84%
Now, you can expand this
to 24 community projects.

00:17:17.109 --> 00:17:19.690 align:middle line:84%
Can you see how much
money our community

00:17:19.690 --> 00:17:24.480 align:middle line:84%
will be bringing in while we're
getting everything for free?

00:17:24.480 --> 00:17:28.010 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
principle of making people

00:17:28.010 --> 00:17:30.960 align:middle line:84%
realize that money is
worthless, that it's not

00:17:30.960 --> 00:17:33.140 align:middle line:84%
the money that keeps
our community going,

00:17:33.140 --> 00:17:34.070 align:middle line:90%
it's ourselves.

00:17:34.070 --> 00:17:36.250 align:middle line:84%
It's the people that
keep the community going.

00:17:36.250 --> 00:17:38.510 align:middle line:84%
We're the ones that are
building and growing and doing

00:17:38.510 --> 00:17:40.170 align:middle line:90%
everything for ourselves.

00:17:40.170 --> 00:17:43.780 align:middle line:84%
And very soon, we realize
we get so much money

00:17:43.780 --> 00:17:46.020 align:middle line:84%
that we can do
anything, while we still

00:17:46.020 --> 00:17:47.170 align:middle line:90%
live in a world with money.

00:17:47.170 --> 00:17:48.840 align:middle line:84%
If we need a new
hospital, the money

00:17:48.840 --> 00:17:50.690 align:middle line:84%
will be available to
build a new hospital.

00:17:50.690 --> 00:17:53.730 align:middle line:84%
Whatever we think we
need do, we can do.

00:17:53.730 --> 00:17:57.750 align:middle line:84%
And this is all driven by what
we call the Council of Elders.

00:17:57.750 --> 00:17:59.890 align:middle line:84%
We have to change
the way we operate.

00:17:59.890 --> 00:18:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And this is where we go back
to the ancient philosophies

00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:05.500 align:middle line:84%
of tribal councils,
where the councils were

00:18:05.500 --> 00:18:07.920 align:middle line:84%
the representative
councils of the people,

00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:11.300 align:middle line:84%
to make decisions that
best benefit the community

00:18:11.300 --> 00:18:14.740 align:middle line:84%
and not benefit individuals
to the detriment

00:18:14.740 --> 00:18:16.810 align:middle line:84%
of the rest of the people
in their community.

00:18:16.810 --> 00:18:19.110 align:middle line:84%
So what we call the
Council of Elders

00:18:19.110 --> 00:18:21.480 align:middle line:84%
is appointed by everyone
in the community

00:18:21.480 --> 00:18:24.360 align:middle line:84%
and consists of the
12 most trusted people

00:18:24.360 --> 00:18:26.910 align:middle line:84%
and individuals
in that community.

00:18:26.910 --> 00:18:29.240 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
transparency comes through,

00:18:29.240 --> 00:18:33.500 align:middle line:84%
again, because everyone will
vote for the Council of Elders

00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:34.400 align:middle line:90%
by their own name.

00:18:34.400 --> 00:18:39.510 align:middle line:84%
So I, Michael, nominate John
to be on the Council of Elders.

00:18:39.510 --> 00:18:41.960 align:middle line:84%
And if John is a
thief and a crook,

00:18:41.960 --> 00:18:43.600 align:middle line:84%
everybody will know
that I have just

00:18:43.600 --> 00:18:46.540 align:middle line:84%
nominated a thief and a crook
onto the Council of Elders.

00:18:46.540 --> 00:18:48.150 align:middle line:90%
So I'll have exposed my motives.

00:18:48.150 --> 00:18:49.640 align:middle line:90%
I'll have exposed myself.

00:18:49.640 --> 00:18:52.140 align:middle line:84%
Once you realize how
transparent this system is,

00:18:52.140 --> 00:18:54.350 align:middle line:84%
you realize that
it's incorruptible

00:18:54.350 --> 00:18:56.700 align:middle line:84%
and that no amount of
money can corrupt it

00:18:56.700 --> 00:18:59.570 align:middle line:84%
because by trying to
corrupt it, you always

00:18:59.570 --> 00:19:02.840 align:middle line:84%
expose yourselves and expose
your ulterior motives.

00:19:02.840 --> 00:19:05.090 align:middle line:84%
And this is ultimately
not where we're going.

00:19:05.090 --> 00:19:07.620 align:middle line:84%
We want to create abundance
by working together.

00:19:07.620 --> 00:19:10.350 align:middle line:84%
And we can only do that
by the simple philosophy

00:19:10.350 --> 00:19:11.790 align:middle line:90%
of cooperation.

00:19:11.790 --> 00:19:17.540 align:middle line:84%
So this contributionist system
is really managed and guided

00:19:17.540 --> 00:19:20.740 align:middle line:84%
by this Council of Elders,
where it's 12 around one.

00:19:20.740 --> 00:19:22.970 align:middle line:84%
The 13th member of
the Council of Elders

00:19:22.970 --> 00:19:25.180 align:middle line:84%
is a spokesperson
for the council.

00:19:25.180 --> 00:19:29.390 align:middle line:84%
And this is how the
community makes decisions

00:19:29.390 --> 00:19:32.890 align:middle line:84%
on a daily basis, hour-by-hour
and minute-by-minute basis.

00:19:32.890 --> 00:19:35.030 align:middle line:84%
If we don't like
something, we take it

00:19:35.030 --> 00:19:36.190 align:middle line:90%
to the Council of Elders.

00:19:36.190 --> 00:19:38.830 align:middle line:84%
And the decision gets
made that same day.

00:19:38.830 --> 00:19:42.240 align:middle line:84%
This is not something that takes
months and years for it to go

00:19:42.240 --> 00:19:44.850 align:middle line:84%
through government or some
body somewhere that sits

00:19:44.850 --> 00:19:47.780 align:middle line:84%
in a crystal palace and makes
decisions about what you can

00:19:47.780 --> 00:19:49.350 align:middle line:90%
and cannot do in your community.

00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:52.070 align:middle line:84%
This is why we say the
Ubuntu philosophy is

00:19:52.070 --> 00:19:54.920 align:middle line:84%
to deconstruct government,
to decentralize

00:19:54.920 --> 00:19:57.960 align:middle line:84%
government, and let
communities run themselves.

00:19:57.960 --> 00:20:00.950 align:middle line:84%
And the Councils of Elders
become the guiding bodies

00:20:00.950 --> 00:20:04.310 align:middle line:84%
that guide and advise
the communities of what's

00:20:04.310 --> 00:20:06.210 align:middle line:84%
best for the
community and what we

00:20:06.210 --> 00:20:09.150 align:middle line:84%
should be doing for the
benefit of the whole community.

00:20:09.150 --> 00:20:12.280 align:middle line:84%
So we create three times
as much as what we need.

00:20:12.280 --> 00:20:14.500 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
abundance comes from.

00:20:14.500 --> 00:20:16.250 align:middle line:84%
This is where we
start destroying

00:20:16.250 --> 00:20:17.470 align:middle line:90%
the capitalist model.

00:20:17.470 --> 00:20:20.720 align:middle line:84%
And this is why I've been
saying that contributionism

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:23.960 align:middle line:84%
devours capitalism
whenever it finds it.

00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:26.750 align:middle line:10%
It is impossible for
any capitalist model

00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:32.610 align:middle line:10%
to exist within the proximity
of a contributionism community.

00:20:32.610 --> 00:20:34.860 align:middle line:10%
